TY  - JOUR
TI  - Resource Depletion Under Technological Uncertainty
AU  - Dasgupta, Partha
AU  - Stiglitz, Joseph
AB  - [The purpose of this paper is to study the effect of uncertainty in the arrival date of a new technology on the rate of depletion of an exhaustible natural resource. It is shown that under a large class of circumstances uncertainty leads to a faster initial depletion rate if the initial resource stock is small and to greater conservation if it is large. A particular kind of certainty equivalence result is proved and the results of the paper are used to comment on possible interpretations of certain historical episodes of resource exhaustion.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1981
